## Setup

### Requirements

```bash
pip install torch transformers pytorch-lightning scikit-learn pandas numpy tqdm boto3 pyautogen openai
```

Tested with Python 3.10, PyTorch 2.1, Transformers 4.38.

### Configuration

Each notebook contains a **CONFIGURATION cell** near the top (cell 2). Update the paths and credentials before running:

```python
# Root directory of this repository
BASE = "your/path/here"

# SemEval-2023 / CheckThat!-2024 data directories
SEMEVAL_DEV_DIR  = "your/path/here"
CHECKTHAT24_DIR  = "your/path/here"

# S3 credentials (if using remote model storage)
os.environ.setdefault("AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID",     "your-access-key-id")
os.environ.setdefault("AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY", "your-secret-access-key")
S3_ENDPOINT = "https://your-s3-endpoint"
S3_BUCKET   = "your-s3-bucket"
```

For Prompt-A and Iter-Ens, set your OpenAI API key:

```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY="your-key-here"
```

### Data access

All datasets used in this work originate from official shared task challenges. Data must be requested or downloaded through the respective challenge platforms and is subject to each organizer's terms of use — it is not redistributed here.

| Resource | Challenge / URL |
|----------|-----------------|
| SemEval 2023 Task 3 | https://propaganda.math.unipd.it/semeval2023task3/ |
| CheckThat! 2024 Task 3 | https://checkthat.gitlab.io/clef2024/task3/ |
| SlavicNLP 2025 | https://bsnlp.cs.helsinki.fi/slavicnlp2025.html |

---

## Running the Experiments

Run notebooks in order within each stage. Stage 2 depends on Stage 1 predictions.

**Stage 1:**
```
stage1_step1  →  stage1_step2  →  stage1_step3 (SR_para)
stage1_step4 (NLI baseline, independent)
stage1_step5 (Prompt-A / Iter-Ens, independent)
stage1_step6 (TCM analysis, after step2 and step5)
```

**Stage 2:**
```
stage2_step1  →  stage2_step2  →  stage2_step3  →  stage2_step4
                                       ↑
                              requires Stage 1 predictions
                              (from stage1_step2 and stage1_step5)
```

**Evaluation:**
```
evaluation/evaluation_span_f1_scorer.ipynb   # standalone, works with any prediction TSV
```

---

## S2-C Training Configuration

| Hyperparameter | Value |
|----------------|-------|
| Backbone | `bert-base-multilingual-cased` (mBERT) |
| Feature layer | L10 (hidden state from layer 10) |
| Output classes | 47 (O + 23 B- + 23 I-) |
| Class weights | O: 0.5 / B- and I-: 2.0 |
| Optimizer | AdamW |
| Learning rate | 6.91 × 10⁻⁵ |
| Weight decay | 3.58 × 10⁻³ |
| Warmup steps | 226 |
| Batch size | 32 |
| Max epochs | 30 |
| Precision | FP16 mixed |
| Sliding window | max_length=256, stride=128 |
| Best checkpoint | Selected by EN span F1 on dev set (optimal epoch: 13) |
| Random seed | 42 |

